<L>__{exterior locksley castle night}
<A>__{steam pours from the nostrils of a black charger. lord locksley mounts, in armor. duncan attempts to detain him.}
<C>__{duncan}
<D>__{you cannot go alone, master. let me ride for help.}
<C>__{locksley}
<D>__{that may be too late. kenneth, lead the way.}
<A>__{he kicks his horse into motion.}
<C>__{duncan}
<D>__{master, stay! there is an evil moon tonight.}
<C>__{locksley}
<D>__{good will overcome, duncan. trust in that.}
<A>__{duncan looks up. crosses himself. dark clouds race across the moon.}
